1
00:00:05,552 --> 00:00:07,850
Oh, look! There's Joey's picture!

2
00:00:08,055 --> 00:00:09,317
This is so exciting!

3
00:00:09,590 --> 00:00:12,616
You can spot someone who's
never seen his plays.

4
00:00:12,826 --> 00:00:16,284
Notice, no fear.
No sense of impending doom.

5
00:00:17,097 --> 00:00:22,194
"The role of man number three
will not be played by Vic Shapiro."

6
00:00:22,403 --> 00:00:24,701
We came on the wrong night.

7
00:00:26,173 --> 00:00:28,539
I can't believe I forgot a magazine.

8
00:00:28,742 --> 00:00:31,734
-Come on, this might be good.
-I don't know.

9
00:00:31,945 --> 00:00:36,780
The exclamation point scares me.
It's not just <i>Freud</i>, it's <i>Freud!</i>

10
00:00:37,951 --> 00:00:39,816
Magic is about to happen!

11
00:00:40,888 --> 00:00:42,412
Well, Eva...

12
00:00:43,190 --> 00:00:46,284
...we've done
some excellent work here.

13
00:00:47,561 --> 00:00:49,290
And I would have to say...

14
00:00:49,830 --> 00:00:53,561
...your problem is quite clear.

15
00:00:55,402 --> 00:00:58,633
<i>All you want is a dinkle</i>

16
00:00:59,006 --> 00:01:01,873
<i>What you envy's a schwang</i>

17
00:01:02,076 --> 00:01:05,477
<i>A thing through which you can tinkle</i>

18
00:01:05,679 --> 00:01:08,307
<i>To play with or simply let hang</i>

19
00:01:23,063 --> 00:01:25,293
The One With the Butt

20
00:02:22,956 --> 00:02:24,924
I feel violated.

21
00:02:25,626 --> 00:02:28,959
Did anybody else feel like
peeling their skin off...

22
00:02:29,163 --> 00:02:31,631
...to have something else to do?

23
00:02:31,832 --> 00:02:32,821
Ross, 10:00.

24
00:02:33,066 --> 00:02:34,795
Is it? It feels like 2.

25
00:02:36,136 --> 00:02:39,697
-No, 10:00!
-What?

26
00:02:39,907 --> 00:02:44,207
There's a beautiful woman
at 8, 9, 10:00!

27
00:02:45,946 --> 00:02:47,140
Hello!

28
00:02:47,414 --> 00:02:53,011
She's amazing! She makes the women I
dream about look like fat, bald men.

29
00:02:53,220 --> 00:02:55,120
Go over.
She's not with anyone.

30
00:02:55,322 --> 00:02:58,780
And what would my opening line be?
Excuse me...

31
00:03:01,361 --> 00:03:03,761
Come on, she's a person.
You can do it.

32
00:03:03,964 --> 00:03:06,933
Could she be more out of my league?
Back me up.

33
00:03:07,167 --> 00:03:10,659
He couldn't get a woman
like that in a million years.

34
00:03:12,139 --> 00:03:15,939
You always see these beautiful
women with "nothing" guys.

35
00:03:16,176 --> 00:03:18,701
You could be one of those guys.

36
00:03:19,079 --> 00:03:21,013
-You could do that.
-You think?

37
00:03:21,281 --> 00:03:22,578
Absolutely!

38
00:03:22,783 --> 00:03:25,115
I can't believe
I'm considering this.

39
00:03:25,319 --> 00:03:27,844
-I'm very aware of my tongue.
-Come on.

40
00:03:28,121 --> 00:03:29,884
Here goes.

41
00:03:30,090 --> 00:03:33,253
Stand back, everyone.
Incoming ego shrapnel.

42
00:03:33,460 --> 00:03:35,951
All right, I can do this.

43
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:41,830
-Yes?
-Hi.

44
00:03:43,370 --> 00:03:45,361
Okay, next word would be...

45
00:03:45,639 --> 00:03:46,628
...Chandler.

46
00:03:47,841 --> 00:03:50,469
Chandler is my name and...

47
00:03:51,011 --> 00:03:52,774
Hi!

48
00:03:54,081 --> 00:03:55,514
Yes, you said that.

49
00:03:55,749 --> 00:03:58,718
Yes! Yes, I did.
But what I didn't say...

50
00:03:58,986 --> 00:04:01,011
What I wanted to say was...

51
00:04:01,221 --> 00:04:04,952
...would you like to go out with me?
Thank you. Good night.

52
00:04:05,158 --> 00:04:06,352
Chandler?

53
00:04:09,930 --> 00:04:13,195
-I didn't know you could dance!
-You were in a play!

54
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:15,300
What'd you think?

55
00:04:15,669 --> 00:04:18,934
-I didn't know you could dance!
-You were in a play!

56
00:04:19,172 --> 00:04:21,732
It wasn't that bad.
I was the lead.

57
00:04:21,942 --> 00:04:26,208
It was better than the troll thing.
At least you got to see my head.

58
00:04:26,413 --> 00:04:28,574
-You're right.
-We saw your head.

59
00:04:29,116 --> 00:04:31,050
How about that accent?

60
00:04:31,251 --> 00:04:36,018
Yeah. All of your W's were V's.

61
00:04:37,557 --> 00:04:38,956
She said yes!

62
00:04:40,394 --> 00:04:44,262
Awful play, man!

63
00:04:44,464 --> 00:04:48,958
Her name's Aurora. She's Italian
and she pronounces my name "Chandler."

64
00:04:50,904 --> 00:04:52,235
I like that better.

65
00:04:52,439 --> 00:04:54,168
The usher gave me this.

66
00:04:54,474 --> 00:04:57,568
-What is it?
-The Estelle Leonard Talent Agency.

67
00:04:57,778 --> 00:05:00,508
An agency left its card.
They wanna sign me!

68
00:05:00,714 --> 00:05:02,272
Based on this play?

69
00:05:04,384 --> 00:05:06,477
Based on this play!

70
00:05:06,687 --> 00:05:08,848
Look! There's a note on the back.

71
00:05:09,056 --> 00:05:12,617
"Loved your work. Call me a sap."

72
00:05:14,528 --> 00:05:16,996
She was obviously very moved!

73
00:05:17,197 --> 00:05:19,688
You should call her fairly quickly.

74
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:22,460
Yeah! As soon as possible!

75
00:05:25,639 --> 00:05:27,197
Come in!

76
00:05:28,408 --> 00:05:30,808
Hi. I'm here to see Estelle Leonard.

77
00:05:31,011 --> 00:05:34,469
Just a moment, let me see
if she's in.

78
00:05:35,449 --> 00:05:37,314
Hello.

79
00:05:38,852 --> 00:05:40,717
-You're Estelle?
-I know...

80
00:05:40,921 --> 00:05:45,381
...you weren't expecting someone
so fantastically beautiful.

81
00:05:47,694 --> 00:05:52,791
Love lump. Take a load off already,
darling. Sit already.

82
00:05:53,100 --> 00:05:56,331
I can't tell you how excited
I am to be here.

83
00:05:56,536 --> 00:05:58,436
Why not?

84
00:05:59,539 --> 00:06:03,805
-What I meant was...
-You don't mind if I eat, do you?

85
00:06:09,049 --> 00:06:10,038
Joey...

86
00:06:10,250 --> 00:06:13,447
...sweetheart, let me ask you
a question.

87
00:06:13,653 --> 00:06:17,316
Did you ever see the movie
<i>Sleepless in Seattle</i>?

88
00:06:17,524 --> 00:06:20,823
-Wow! Do you represent those actors?
-No.

89
00:06:21,294 --> 00:06:24,730
But you know the end,
where they're happy?

90
00:06:24,931 --> 00:06:27,559
That's gonna be you and me.

91
00:06:28,502 --> 00:06:30,402
You mean you wanna sign me?

92
00:06:30,604 --> 00:06:35,940
No, I wanna go to the top of the
Empire State Building and make out.

93
00:06:36,810 --> 00:06:38,869
Of course I wanna sign you!

94
00:06:39,646 --> 00:06:42,080
-Miss Leonard, I'm so...
-Oh, boy.

95
00:06:42,282 --> 00:06:45,115
-Ride them, cowboy.
-I'm sorry!

96
00:06:55,228 --> 00:06:58,356
I don't see it!

97
00:06:59,933 --> 00:07:03,096
-Try to look through it.
-Unfocus your eyes.

98
00:07:03,303 --> 00:07:05,863
Focus? There's nothing to focus on.

99
00:07:06,540 --> 00:07:09,998
-It's the Statue of Liberty!
-Right!

100
00:07:10,210 --> 00:07:13,077
-Where's the Statue of Liberty?
-There.

101
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:15,043
I can't not see it now.

102
00:07:17,050 --> 00:07:18,074
Hey, kids!

103
00:07:18,285 --> 00:07:20,651
Come here. Do you see anything here?

104
00:07:20,854 --> 00:07:24,255
-It looks like a boat.
-A boat.

105
00:07:24,458 --> 00:07:27,325
Right in front of
the Statue of Liberty.

106
00:07:29,196 --> 00:07:33,724
It's been seven seconds, and you
haven't asked me how my date went.

107
00:07:33,934 --> 00:07:36,198
How was your date, Chandler?

108
00:07:36,403 --> 00:07:37,700
It was unbelievable!

109
00:07:37,904 --> 00:07:41,533
I've never met anyone like her.
She's had an amazing life!

110
00:07:41,741 --> 00:07:43,572
<i>She was in the Israeli army.</i>

111
00:07:43,777 --> 00:07:48,305
None of the bullets hit the engine,
so we made it to the border.

112
00:07:48,515 --> 00:07:51,075
But just barely, and I...

113
00:07:51,284 --> 00:07:55,345
I've been talking about myself
all night long. I'm sorry.

114
00:07:55,555 --> 00:07:57,750
What about you? Tell me a story.

115
00:07:58,525 --> 00:08:00,720
All right, once...

116
00:08:00,927 --> 00:08:02,724
...I got on the subway.

117
00:08:02,929 --> 00:08:04,726
And it was at night...

118
00:08:04,931 --> 00:08:08,059
...and I rode it all the way
to Brooklyn.

119
00:08:08,268 --> 00:08:10,566
Just for the hell of it.

120
00:08:11,071 --> 00:08:13,699
We talked until 2:00. It was perfect.

121
00:08:14,741 --> 00:08:15,765
More or less.

122
00:08:16,042 --> 00:08:18,442
Suddenly, we realized we were
in Yemen.

123
00:08:18,845 --> 00:08:20,437
I'm sorry, so "we" is...?

124
00:08:21,214 --> 00:08:22,545
"We" is me and Rick.

125
00:08:22,749 --> 00:08:23,738
Who's Rick?

126
00:08:23,950 --> 00:08:25,247
Who's Rick?

127
00:08:26,453 --> 00:08:27,477
My husband.

128
00:08:30,190 --> 00:08:33,318
-Oh, so you're divorced?
-No.

129
00:08:33,527 --> 00:08:37,657
I'm sorry. So you're widowed?
Hopefully?

130
00:08:37,864 --> 00:08:40,332
No, I'm still married.

131
00:08:41,001 --> 00:08:45,631
So, how would your husband feel
about you sitting here with me...

132
00:08:45,839 --> 00:08:51,141
...sliding your foot so far up my leg
you can count the change in my pocket?

133
00:08:52,279 --> 00:08:53,678
Don't worry.

134
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:57,577
He'd be okay with you
because he's okay with Ethan.

135
00:08:58,451 --> 00:09:00,851
Ethan? There's an Ethan?

136
00:09:01,988 --> 00:09:05,424
Ethan is my boyfriend.

137
00:09:05,625 --> 00:09:06,785
What?

138
00:09:08,862 --> 00:09:12,229
What kind of relationship
do you imagine us having...

139
00:09:12,432 --> 00:09:15,401
...if you have a husband
and a boyfriend?

140
00:09:15,602 --> 00:09:18,730
I suppose, mainly sexual.

141
00:09:21,675 --> 00:09:23,302
Sorry it didn't work out.

142
00:09:23,543 --> 00:09:26,808
What, not work out?
I'm seeing her again on Thursday.

143
00:09:27,013 --> 00:09:29,641
Didn't you listen to the story?

144
00:09:30,917 --> 00:09:33,351
Didn't you listen? It's twisted!

145
00:09:33,553 --> 00:09:35,783
How could you get involved
with her?

146
00:09:35,989 --> 00:09:39,891
I had trouble with it at first.
But I get the good stuff.

147
00:09:40,093 --> 00:09:43,062
All the fun, all the talking,
all the sex...

148
00:09:43,263 --> 00:09:46,096
...and none of the responsibility.

149
00:09:46,533 --> 00:09:49,696
-This is every guy's fantasy!
-That's not true!

150
00:09:49,903 --> 00:09:53,634
-Ross, is this your fantasy?
-No, of course not.

151
00:09:55,375 --> 00:09:57,172
Yeah. Yeah, it is.

152
00:09:58,044 --> 00:10:01,536
You'd go out with someone
going out with someone else?

153
00:10:02,015 --> 00:10:04,040
-I couldn't.
-Good for you.

154
00:10:04,284 --> 00:10:06,775
When I'm with a woman,
I need to know...

155
00:10:06,987 --> 00:10:09,922
...I'm going out
with more people than her.

156
00:10:10,423 --> 00:10:13,859
Once, I went out with a guy who
just got divorced.

157
00:10:14,060 --> 00:10:17,427
It was hard. His kids liked me
better than him.

158
00:10:17,631 --> 00:10:20,293
What does this have to do
with Chandler?

159
00:10:21,167 --> 00:10:22,964
Nothing.

160
00:10:23,303 --> 00:10:25,965
I didn't have anything
on that topic.

161
00:10:26,172 --> 00:10:28,299
So I went another way.

162
00:10:29,275 --> 00:10:33,211
You know, monogamy can be
a tricky concept.

163
00:10:33,413 --> 00:10:36,348
I mean, anthropologically speaking...

164
00:10:37,717 --> 00:10:39,844
Fine. Now you'll never know.

165
00:10:40,053 --> 00:10:41,680
We're kidding. Tell us.

166
00:10:41,921 --> 00:10:43,479
-We wanna know.
-Come on!

167
00:10:43,690 --> 00:10:47,524
All right. There's a theory
put forth by Richard Leakey...

168
00:10:58,638 --> 00:11:01,835
Are we greeting each other
this way now? I like it.

169
00:11:03,476 --> 00:11:05,137
Look! I cleaned!

170
00:11:05,345 --> 00:11:07,609
I did the windows.
I did the floors.

171
00:11:07,847 --> 00:11:12,807
I used all the vacuum attachments but
the round one. What's it for?

172
00:11:13,019 --> 00:11:16,216
Nobody knows.
And we're not supposed to ask.

173
00:11:16,423 --> 00:11:17,549
What do you think?

174
00:11:17,791 --> 00:11:21,249
-It's very clean.
-Really, it looks great!

175
00:11:25,098 --> 00:11:27,692
I see you moved the green ottoman.

176
00:11:31,504 --> 00:11:33,062
How did that happen?

177
00:11:34,474 --> 00:11:37,034
I don't know. It looked better there.

178
00:11:37,844 --> 00:11:40,608
And it's an extra seat
around the table.

179
00:11:41,147 --> 00:11:42,910
Yeah, it's interesting.

180
00:11:44,584 --> 00:11:46,848
But you know what? Just for fun...

181
00:11:47,187 --> 00:11:50,679
...let's see what it looked like
in the old spot.

182
00:11:51,491 --> 00:11:53,152
Just to compare.

183
00:11:53,359 --> 00:11:54,656
Let's see.

184
00:11:55,095 --> 00:11:56,995
Well, it looks good there too.

185
00:11:57,397 --> 00:11:59,524
Let's leave it there for a while.

186
00:12:00,533 --> 00:12:03,900
I can't believe you moved
the green ottoman.

187
00:12:04,504 --> 00:12:08,941
Be glad you didn't fan the magazines.
She'll scratch your eyes out.

188
00:12:09,142 --> 00:12:12,373
-You guys, I am not that bad!
-Yeah, you are.

189
00:12:13,780 --> 00:12:17,272
Remember, I lived with you?
You were a little...

190
00:12:21,454 --> 00:12:22,751
That is so unfair!

191
00:12:22,956 --> 00:12:27,984
When we were kids, yours was the only
Raggedy Ann doll that wasn't raggedy.

192
00:12:29,462 --> 00:12:32,090
Okay, so I'm responsible.
I'm organized.

193
00:12:32,332 --> 00:12:34,323
But hey, I can be a kook!

194
00:12:36,569 --> 00:12:38,628
All right, you madcap gal!

195
00:12:40,406 --> 00:12:41,498
Imagine this.

196
00:12:41,775 --> 00:12:45,711
The phone bill arrives,
but you don't pay it right away.

197
00:12:45,912 --> 00:12:48,437
-Why not?
-Because you're a kook!

198
00:12:50,550 --> 00:12:53,348
You wait until they send a notice.

199
00:12:54,087 --> 00:12:55,452
I could do that.

200
00:12:55,655 --> 00:12:59,682
Okay, then you let me
go grocery shopping...

201
00:12:59,893 --> 00:13:03,158
-No problem.
-I'm not done yet.

202
00:13:03,696 --> 00:13:08,599
And I buy detergent, but it's not
the one with the easy-pour spout.

203
00:13:08,802 --> 00:13:11,430
Why would someone do that?

204
00:13:12,572 --> 00:13:15,040
One might wonder.

205
00:13:15,842 --> 00:13:19,107
But I would be fine with that.

206
00:13:19,312 --> 00:13:24,011
A glass is on the table with no
coaster. A cold drink. A hot day.

207
00:13:24,684 --> 00:13:29,018
Beads of condensation are inching
closer to the wood...

208
00:13:29,222 --> 00:13:30,314
Stop it!

209
00:13:34,060 --> 00:13:35,322
Oh, my God!

210
00:13:35,762 --> 00:13:37,696
It's true. Who am I?

211
00:13:38,231 --> 00:13:40,222
Monica, you're Mom.

212
00:13:48,608 --> 00:13:49,666
Oh, my God!

213
00:13:52,345 --> 00:13:54,074
Okay, I'll be there.

214
00:13:56,416 --> 00:13:58,008
That was my agent.

215
00:13:59,953 --> 00:14:05,914
My agent has just gotten me a job
in the new Al Pacino movie!

216
00:14:06,125 --> 00:14:08,889
-That's great!
-What's the part?

217
00:14:09,095 --> 00:14:13,225
Can you believe it? Pacino!
This guy's why I became an actor!

218
00:14:13,433 --> 00:14:19,201
"Out of order? You're out of order!
This whole courtroom's out of order!"

219
00:14:19,806 --> 00:14:21,569
Seriously, what's the part?

220
00:14:21,774 --> 00:14:25,471
"Just when I thought I was out,
they pull me back in!"

221
00:14:25,745 --> 00:14:28,805
Come on. Seriously, Joey,
what's the part?

222
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:32,342
You're... What?

223
00:14:34,921 --> 00:14:38,152
I'm his butt double, okay?

224
00:14:41,728 --> 00:14:44,356
I play Al Pacino's butt.

225
00:14:46,532 --> 00:14:49,763
All right? He goes into the shower,
and then...

226
00:14:50,069 --> 00:14:52,060
...I'm his butt.

227
00:14:52,438 --> 00:14:53,598
Oh, my God!

228
00:14:53,907 --> 00:14:55,067
Come on, you guys.

229
00:14:55,341 --> 00:14:58,606
It's a real Pacino movie
and that's big!

230
00:14:58,878 --> 00:15:01,472
It's terrific. You deserve this.

231
00:15:01,681 --> 00:15:06,516
After years of struggling you've
cracked your way into show business.

232
00:15:09,289 --> 00:15:11,621
Fine. Make jokes, I don't care.

233
00:15:11,824 --> 00:15:15,316
-This is a big break for me!
-You're right. It is.

234
00:15:16,462 --> 00:15:19,488
So, will you invite us
to the big opening?

235
00:15:29,309 --> 00:15:32,244
-I need some moisturizer.
-For what?

236
00:15:32,445 --> 00:15:34,470
Today's the big day!

237
00:15:37,150 --> 00:15:40,381
You got any tweezers? I think
I have a rogue hair.

238
00:15:41,020 --> 00:15:43,955
God. Go in the bathroom.
Use whatever you want.

239
00:15:44,157 --> 00:15:46,990
Don't ever tell me what you did
in there.

240
00:15:47,193 --> 00:15:48,888
Thank you.

241
00:15:50,663 --> 00:15:53,461
-Joey's mom's on the phone.
-In the bathroom.

242
00:15:53,666 --> 00:15:57,227
-You don't wanna go in there!
-Come on, we're roommates.

243
00:15:58,538 --> 00:16:01,029
My eyes! My eyes!

244
00:16:03,609 --> 00:16:05,236
I warned you.

245
00:16:05,445 --> 00:16:07,140
Who is being loud?

246
00:16:07,347 --> 00:16:09,110
Oh, that would be Monica.

247
00:16:09,882 --> 00:16:13,010
Can I borrow stuff?
I wanna make Aurora breakfast.

248
00:16:13,219 --> 00:16:15,016
You got the whole night?

249
00:16:15,221 --> 00:16:18,213
Well, I only have 20 minutes
